From peirce Michael Peirce Subject Re Sales of PowerBook slowing In article tohi martin tohi Jean francois Martin writes First this is not an April A dealer in my town told me that the PowerBook don't sell as they use to The guy told me that Apple is having the same problem it has when the desktop Mac was too expensive the PowerBook are too expensive in comparison to what you can get on the DOS What do you think of this Do you feel the same thing about it Just Sounds about If there is high demand for a product there is little incentive to aggresively cut Once the demand fall off a bit then is the time to start getting aggressive with Waiting too long can really hurt your business though The PowerBooks have sold very well up to now if they are slowing down Apple needs to come out with some lower priced versions the only reason I own a PowerBook is that I could spring for a the rest of the lineup is way to pricey for me I'd bet they'll be coming out with more power versions Michael Peirce Peirce Software Suite Hibiscus Place San Jose California USA Makers of voice fax Smoothie AppleLink peirce America Online AFC Peirce